You missed the whole point on which tank is better when the crap hits the fan.<br>
<br>
Sure, the warrior can stand there and mash his taunt button and pray for some good procs...but if the messer ain't quick and/or the slower can't get the mobs slowed quick enough, the warrior is goona go down, the chanter is going to go down, the healer is going to go down...or any combination of the three: your whole group is gonna wipe out.<br>
<br>
When the crap hits the fan and your tank is a paladin, the paladin really gets a chance to shine.  <br>
<br>
If the problem is a bad pull, he can root the extra mobs before they get into camp: a little ghetto CC can go a long way towards helping the real CC get a grip on things.  <br>
<br>
Cleric LD in the middle of a fight? Sucks to be the warrior.  The paladin? He can chain stun the mob while the rest of the group deals damage - giving your LD cleric time to get back on AND FIND HIS GROUP STILL ALIVE <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  <br>
<br>
Pulled more than one mob?  Lost agro when the cleric dropped a CH??  If the mob turns on your cleric the paladin can stun the to gain agro - while the warrior is praying for a proc. Or, if that doesn't work, the paladin can use his LH to keep the cleric from dying. The warrior's biggest move here is going to be AE Taunt - comparable, but not as versatile as the Paladin skill set.<br>
<br>
There are definately cases in Everquest where you really want (sometimes NEED!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) a warrior as your tank, but when the crap really hits the fan, I would rather be playing the paladin, where I have a chance to DO something about the situation - not just stand there and whack my Taunt button and hope that the other players in the group can save our butts.<br>
<br>
Just the opinion of one Warrior/Paladin....your milage will vary.<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=331441"> Tappy Thistlebloom </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
