<br>
I've been grouped with alot of paladin going from the really low spectrum of equipement (windblade) up to those using emp 2-hander.  In general, visible dps from a a paladin from the back is lower then me from the front.<br>
<br>
Exception to this is on undead where a paladin will likely do warrior dmg on avg.  When the paladin is tanking and I'm attacking from the back, the ratio can go to me doing 50% more dmg to up to twice the dmg in some case.<br>
<br>
One thing that people really seem to underevaluate is that in pop, taunt &quot;do&quot; work alot.  <br>
<br>
Well, I don't necessarily hate paladins, but in my experience most group set up do not need any outside help as far as healing is concerned.  DPS is the prime factor for me.<br>
<br>
Even thought tanking in xp group paladin can do just fine as long as equipement is similar, their dps is lower.  To me, it means that a group using a paladin as a tank will kills mobs slower, and gains less xp.<br>
<br>
@#%$ can hit the fans in a different ways.  But when you pull 3 mobs, that a ch land and the 3 unslowed mobs jump the cleric.  You have a situation where not much can be done.  The only thing a paladin alone can do is lay on hands on the cleric.  Anything else will results in the cleric death.  Enchanter can ae mez, the cleric himself can DA, the warrior can move there and AE taunt as long as the cleric health is above 2 bubble or so it should work.  SK will most likely FD and pull the corpse for CR.  That's just 1 example, but to think that paladin's hability to save a group out of instant danger is superior to warrior that much is ignorant at best.<br>
<br>
Just rambling here.<br>
<br>
Thorbadin<br>
