<br>
Like someone mentioned, Taunt actually works pretty well in PoP.  It's neat that Paladins can stun mobs for aggro but it's hardly necessary if you're just doing boring XP grind.<br>
<br>
Also, on stuns, unless the Paladin is timing them carefully, you don't really save that much damage versus slowed mobs since their delay can recycle while stunned.  Also it just doesn't make that much of a difference whether a slowed mob is stunned or not.  For unslowed mob, PoP mobs dish out too much damage that it's just unfeasible to tank them for long period of time without slow for anyone.  The only place where stuns would really matter is on unslowable mobs (but you rarely XP on those) or if your slower is having problem getting slow to stick. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90049">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daxos92>Daxos92</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/2/02 9:59:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2568.topic&index=25>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ac.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Paladin best tank?</span><hr size=1> Much like comparing warrior to warrior on who is a better tank, it's all about the gear <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
